WEBVTT

00:02:51.376 --> 00:02:54.462
Are you okay sharing the unit
with someone else?

00:02:54.963 --> 00:02:57.173
Hi. I'm Lorelei Rios.

00:03:02.178 --> 00:03:03.428
Loki Mendez.

00:03:03.429 --> 00:03:06.641
What was that incident
you're running away from?

00:03:10.770 --> 00:03:12.606
I feel like we're gonna be BFFs.

00:03:18.277 --> 00:03:19.591
Here he goes again.

00:03:19.624 --> 00:03:21.042
I need to report this.

00:03:26.552 --> 00:03:28.637
Looks like I went into the wrong room.

00:03:28.662 --> 00:03:29.830
I believe I can help you.

00:03:41.133 --> 00:03:42.675
Because of some worthless guy.

00:03:42.676 --> 00:03:43.802
Take back what you said!

00:03:45.429 --> 00:03:47.640
I want you to join the Q.E.D. Club.

00:03:52.770 --> 00:03:53.854
Ma’am! Sir!

00:03:54.271 --> 00:03:55.480
You're not allowed to be here.

00:03:55.481 --> 00:03:56.481
Come down now.

00:03:57.024 --> 00:04:00.277
If anything happens to you here,
the school will be accountable.

00:04:13.707 --> 00:04:15.292
Does your silence mean yes?

00:04:17.419 --> 00:04:18.579
You're really something, huh?

00:04:19.046 --> 00:04:20.046
Is this a prank?

00:04:20.339 --> 00:04:24.468
Of all people, why did you pick me
to join your detective club?

00:04:25.844 --> 00:04:28.389
The Student Council
wants to shutdown Q.E.D. Club.

00:04:29.515 --> 00:04:31.308
They said there aren't any other members.

00:04:32.559 --> 00:04:34.436
My club needs to have another member

00:04:34.644 --> 00:04:36.646
or else, they’ll take away my club room.

00:04:37.398 --> 00:04:39.566
Okay, so why is that my problem?

00:04:39.817 --> 00:04:40.817
You're right.

00:04:41.652 --> 00:04:42.695
It’s not your problem.

00:04:43.821 --> 00:04:45.447
It’s the favor you owe me.

00:04:46.615 --> 00:04:48.575
In exchange for helping you with Linda.

00:04:49.159 --> 00:04:50.619
Her name is Lisa,

00:04:50.786 --> 00:04:51.914
not Linda.

00:04:51.954 --> 00:04:54.747
Also, of all the things you could ask me,

00:04:54.748 --> 00:04:55.833
why did it have to be this?

00:04:56.500 --> 00:04:57.883
Is there nothing else?

00:04:57.960 --> 00:04:59.293
I mean, I don't know.

00:04:59.294 --> 00:05:03.674
I can run you some school errands
or get you one month free coffee.

00:05:03.841 --> 00:05:06.635
- Or something...
- Unless, you can give me my own club room.

00:05:07.720 --> 00:05:09.179
I don't need those.

00:05:10.222 --> 00:05:13.308
The Student Council Vice President
is bullying me.

00:05:14.393 --> 00:05:16.060
He knows it will be hard for me

00:05:16.061 --> 00:05:17.520
to pursuade anyone

00:05:17.521 --> 00:05:18.772
to join my club.

00:05:19.231 --> 00:05:20.983
That's why he ordered the shutdown.

00:05:22.026 --> 00:05:25.236
Look, whatever your issue is
with the Student Council VP,

00:05:25.237 --> 00:05:26.655
that’s none of my business.

00:05:26.864 --> 00:05:29.866
But I can’t join the Q.E.D. Club.

00:05:29.867 --> 00:05:32.494
Because I don't know anything
about solving mysteries.

00:05:32.911 --> 00:05:34.121
I’m not meant for that.

00:05:35.539 --> 00:05:36.999
But you have a talent for writing.

00:05:37.541 --> 00:05:38.541
Right?

00:05:39.001 --> 00:05:40.002
You have a blog.

00:05:40.753 --> 00:05:41.753
Yes?

00:05:41.837 --> 00:05:42.837
So what?

00:05:43.213 --> 00:05:45.673
The Q.E.D. Club is the perfect avenue

00:05:45.674 --> 00:05:47.676
to showcase your journalist skills.

00:05:48.385 --> 00:05:49.385
Just saying.

00:06:01.148 --> 00:06:04.233
Today, he asked me to join his club.

00:06:04.234 --> 00:06:06.778
I don't even know why I
told him I owe him a favor.

00:06:06.803 --> 00:06:10.098
After all, he's the one
who actually wronged me.

00:07:29.309 --> 00:07:30.348
Loki?

00:07:31.871 --> 00:07:33.020
Loki?

00:07:48.661 --> 00:07:50.580
♪ Shadows. ♪

00:07:51.583 --> 00:07:54.294
♪ Creeping slowly through the dark. ♪

00:07:55.003 --> 00:07:59.048
♪ Watching, blocking, like. ♪

00:07:59.049 --> 00:08:02.594
♪ You can't even take a step. ♪

00:08:03.553 --> 00:08:07.139
♪ Every cry, every shake. ♪

00:08:07.140 --> 00:08:10.309
♪ Only walls reflect the ache. ♪

00:08:10.310 --> 00:08:13.270
♪ All the echoes burn inside. ♪

00:08:13.271 --> 00:08:17.776
♪ Like fire and bullets in the past. ♪

00:08:19.152 --> 00:08:21.279
♪ Listen to the warnings. ♪

00:08:22.531 --> 00:08:24.908
♪ Threats are drawing near. ♪

00:08:25.992 --> 00:08:29.663
♪ This is not the world you thought. ♪

00:08:30.330 --> 00:08:32.957
♪ You would know. ♪

00:08:32.958 --> 00:08:35.418
♪ Listen to the warnings. ♪

00:08:36.419 --> 00:08:38.547
♪ Open up your eyes. ♪

00:08:39.840 --> 00:08:43.385
♪ This is not the world you thought. ♪

00:08:44.094 --> 00:08:46.637
♪ You would know. ♪

00:08:46.638 --> 00:08:51.476
♪ Listen to the warnings. ♪

00:08:56.269 --> 00:08:57.269
Act normal.

00:08:58.936 --> 00:08:59.936
Okay.

00:09:02.998 --> 00:09:03.998
Okay.

00:10:23.799 --> 00:10:24.805
Lori.

00:10:24.830 --> 00:10:25.372
Why?

00:10:25.372 --> 00:10:26.372
What's your problem?

00:10:26.834 --> 00:10:27.877
What...

00:10:28.307 --> 00:10:29.352
Sorry, Tita.

00:10:29.377 --> 00:10:32.003
- What, do you think I'm a ghost?
- No, Tita. I’m sorry.

00:10:32.546 --> 00:10:34.671
I just get startled easily, that's all.

00:10:35.215 --> 00:10:36.466
How was your sleep?

00:10:37.426 --> 00:10:39.177
You might be lacking rest.

00:10:39.766 --> 00:10:41.642
That's why you're jumpy.

00:10:42.097 --> 00:10:44.391
You know how staying up late
messes with you, kids.

00:10:45.183 --> 00:10:46.393
Acutally, Tita...

00:10:46.977 --> 00:10:48.978
I feel kinda uncomfortable here.

00:10:48.979 --> 00:10:51.106
That’s why I can’t fall asleep right away.

00:10:51.648 --> 00:10:54.316
Do you want me to change
your mattress or pillow?

00:10:54.317 --> 00:10:55.609
Oh, no need.

00:10:55.610 --> 00:10:57.487
My pillow and bed are fine.

00:10:58.655 --> 00:11:00.240
It’s just...

00:11:00.699 --> 00:11:04.744
I think I hear rustling
in the ceiling and walls.

00:11:05.078 --> 00:11:06.746
That’s why I can’t fall asleep.

00:11:07.330 --> 00:11:11.084
But maybe it’s just my imagination,
so don’t mind me.

00:11:12.017 --> 00:11:16.355
I'm not trying to make you more scared,
but I just want to tell you that…

00:11:17.933 --> 00:11:20.184
I hear noises at night, too.

00:11:20.209 --> 00:11:21.209
Huh?

00:11:21.353 --> 00:11:22.979
Really, Tita?

00:11:23.105 --> 00:11:25.065
So it's not just my imagination?

00:11:26.108 --> 00:11:28.568
That’s what the other tenants told me too.

00:11:29.361 --> 00:11:30.779
What can I do?

00:11:31.113 --> 00:11:33.782
I don't know how to deal with spirits.

00:11:34.741 --> 00:11:36.493
This place's already been blessed.

00:11:36.573 --> 00:11:39.159
Three times already.
But it’s still the same.

00:11:42.074 --> 00:11:43.659
Maybe that’s the reason

00:11:44.419 --> 00:11:46.213
why no one stays long

00:11:46.589 --> 00:11:49.175
in your unit with Loki.

00:11:50.296 --> 00:11:53.382
They say the loudest creaks
are in your unit.

00:11:54.533 --> 00:11:55.784
But don't worry,

00:11:56.858 --> 00:12:00.987
because I always include all
my tenants in my prayers.

00:12:02.185 --> 00:12:03.372
That’s why I’m sure,

00:12:03.520 --> 00:12:05.147
it's just creaks, that's all.

00:12:06.189 --> 00:12:07.189
Because

00:12:07.649 --> 00:12:10.694
you’re all protected by my prayers.

00:12:12.320 --> 00:12:14.488
Oh, Tita, I have to go now.

00:12:14.489 --> 00:12:16.366
I'm sorry. Bye!

00:12:32.132 --> 00:12:35.093
What if bad luck is actually chasing me?

00:12:36.136 --> 00:12:39.347
Or worse, what if I’m the bad luck?

00:12:40.640 --> 00:12:43.018
It's like every world I step into...

00:12:43.852 --> 00:12:45.520
I end up messing things up.

00:12:47.189 --> 00:12:48.940
When will this ever end?

00:12:51.151 --> 00:12:53.487
I can't believe
I'm entering this room again.

00:12:54.696 --> 00:12:59.367
The same room that witnessed
how Aaron stalked me.

00:12:59.910 --> 00:13:03.622
I’m new here,
and I’m already in trouble again.

00:13:22.432 --> 00:13:23.891
Okay, guys. Settle down.

00:13:23.892 --> 00:13:25.185
Go back to your seats.

00:13:27.103 --> 00:13:29.564
It's only been a few weeks
this semester, guys,

00:13:30.273 --> 00:13:31.733
but we already have a lot of issues.

00:13:32.901 --> 00:13:34.444
Put yourselves together, huh?

00:13:35.278 --> 00:13:37.614
Focus on your studies.

00:13:38.073 --> 00:13:39.633
Not just on things that stress you out.

00:13:40.742 --> 00:13:42.244
Yes, sir.

00:13:43.453 --> 00:13:44.453
Attendance call.

00:13:45.413 --> 00:13:46.539
Byron, Kelvin?

00:13:46.540 --> 00:13:47.541
Present, sir!

00:13:47.874 --> 00:13:50.085
- Dela Cruz, John Paul?
- Present!

00:13:50.544 --> 00:13:51.753
Flores, Aaron?

00:13:54.548 --> 00:13:55.632
Sorry, I forgot.

00:13:56.466 --> 00:13:58.635
- Galang, Mary Jane?
- Present, sir!

00:13:59.427 --> 00:14:00.887
Jocson, Lisa Claire?

00:14:01.137 --> 00:14:04.015
Sir, she’s absent today
because of yesterday’s incident.

00:14:05.016 --> 00:14:06.226
Roque, Aina?

00:14:06.643 --> 00:14:07.643
Present!

00:14:07.686 --> 00:14:10.187
- Reyes, Von Andy?
- Present.

00:14:14.317 --> 00:14:18.697
Girl, just a reminder,
the org application deadline's on Friday.

00:14:18.863 --> 00:14:19.990
You have to decide.

00:14:20.365 --> 00:14:22.492
Is it really mandatory to join the org?

00:14:22.701 --> 00:14:24.118
Of course!

00:14:24.119 --> 00:14:26.579
What else are you gonna do here,
just study?

00:14:26.580 --> 00:14:27.956
That'd be so boring.

00:14:28.498 --> 00:14:33.628
And didn't the dean say
orgs cover 30 percent of our grade?

00:14:33.962 --> 00:14:35.797
That'd be such a waste if it happens.

00:14:36.798 --> 00:14:37.798
Okay, fine.

00:14:38.258 --> 00:14:41.386
But I was hoping for something more chill.

00:14:42.387 --> 00:14:43.096
How about you?

00:14:43.263 --> 00:14:44.514
What org did you join?

00:14:45.307 --> 00:14:46.933
Oh, I'm switching clubs.

00:14:47.183 --> 00:14:49.518
I didn’t like the club I joined last year.

00:14:49.519 --> 00:14:50.687
Why?

00:14:51.479 --> 00:14:53.606
There’s no thrill, Gardening Club.

00:14:53.607 --> 00:14:56.900
Like, I don’t know
if it’s just me or what.

00:14:56.901 --> 00:14:59.320
But it feels like
they're training me to be old.

00:14:59.321 --> 00:15:03.824
I'm still young.
Why turn me into a plantita at this age?

00:15:03.825 --> 00:15:06.243
So I feel like it has a
purpose and everything.

00:15:06.244 --> 00:15:08.120
But going to class?

00:15:08.121 --> 00:15:09.872
I want something with thrill,

00:15:09.873 --> 00:15:12.041
something that excites me
when I go to school.

00:15:12.042 --> 00:15:13.376
Something that will hype me up.

00:15:13.710 --> 00:15:17.422
You know, we can join
the Paranormal Club together...

00:15:21.885 --> 00:15:24.304
Sure, Rosetta.
Let's join the Paranormal Club.

00:15:24.554 --> 00:15:26.764
Yeah, Lori. That'd be fun, right?

00:15:26.765 --> 00:15:29.183
Especially if we're together
and there's a thrill.

00:15:29.184 --> 00:15:30.518
Perfect. Right?

00:15:31.102 --> 00:15:34.141
Yeah! I'm in. I'll hand in my application.
We can go together!

00:15:42.697 --> 00:15:43.632
Sorry!

00:15:43.657 --> 00:15:45.116
No. It’s okay.

00:15:45.715 --> 00:15:47.424
- I’m new here.
- Oh, okay.

00:15:47.449 --> 00:15:49.993
I’m just looking
for Foreign Affairs Office.

00:15:50.018 --> 00:15:51.230
Oh, okay.

00:15:51.390 --> 00:15:52.759
Well, I’m also new here.

00:15:53.083 --> 00:15:56.619
But I think it might be
in the other building.

00:15:57.545 --> 00:15:58.629
Oh, thank you so much.

00:15:58.630 --> 00:15:59.547
Oh, okay. Yeah.

00:15:59.548 --> 00:16:01.814
- Well, I see you around. No problem.
- Yeah. See you!

00:16:08.378 --> 00:16:11.186
Hi. Join our club, okay?

00:16:15.420 --> 00:16:17.713
Hi. Maybe you'd like some of our flowers?

00:16:17.738 --> 00:16:19.405
Maybe you want tomato???

00:16:19.430 --> 00:16:20.640
There are more here.

00:16:21.361 --> 00:16:22.538
Come, join!

00:16:23.003 --> 00:16:25.254
Hi. Join the Cyber Club.

00:16:25.279 --> 00:16:26.989
Please join the Cyber Club!

00:16:34.040 --> 00:16:35.040
Clarion?

00:16:36.376 --> 00:16:38.670
Okay, I'll think about it. I have to go.

00:16:43.591 --> 00:16:44.591
Okay.

00:16:45.176 --> 00:16:46.969
Young Traveler's Club.

00:16:46.970 --> 00:16:50.264
- Lori! Why did you leave me at the locker?
- Rosetta.

00:16:50.265 --> 00:16:52.182
Sorry. I thought you were following me.

00:16:52.183 --> 00:16:55.437
Come on. Let's join here. Let's go!

00:16:55.645 --> 00:16:56.854
There are many demons here.

00:16:56.855 --> 00:16:59.357
Come on! Let's go inside!

00:16:59.941 --> 00:17:00.941
Hi!

00:17:04.988 --> 00:17:07.281
- Look.
- What's this?

00:17:07.531 --> 00:17:09.032
Paranormal Club!

00:17:18.334 --> 00:17:21.086
Come on. Let’s join this.

00:17:21.087 --> 00:17:22.671
Hold on. It's just...

00:17:22.672 --> 00:17:25.717
I’m not sure yet.
Besides, I don’t have a third eye.

00:17:26.176 --> 00:17:29.763
Even with just two eyes, it's fine.
You can still join our club.

00:17:31.556 --> 00:17:33.849
That's right. Stay here. It’s fun here.

00:17:33.850 --> 00:17:36.518
Yeah, this is very thrilling.

00:17:36.519 --> 00:17:38.729
They've got ghost-hunting activities.

00:17:38.730 --> 00:17:41.107
Come on, let's join.

00:18:13.515 --> 00:18:15.183
Can you be more careful with that?

00:18:15.558 --> 00:18:17.477
What if that hit me?

00:18:17.769 --> 00:18:18.769
Why?

00:18:18.978 --> 00:18:19.978
Did it hit you?

00:18:20.480 --> 00:18:21.480
It didn’t, right?

00:18:21.898 --> 00:18:23.024
You’re not my target.

00:18:23.775 --> 00:18:24.775
Whatever!

00:18:24.984 --> 00:18:25.985
As expected...

00:18:27.028 --> 00:18:28.696
you won’t see me in the club room.

00:18:29.531 --> 00:18:30.865
And you'll still go home early.

00:18:32.367 --> 00:18:33.367
No way.

00:18:33.910 --> 00:18:35.662
I just really want to rest.

00:18:36.204 --> 00:18:37.204
Why?

00:18:37.580 --> 00:18:38.665
Maybe you're wondering.

00:18:39.207 --> 00:18:40.917
I transferred my work place here.

00:18:41.876 --> 00:18:44.076
Since they're kicking me out
of the club room very soon.

00:18:44.295 --> 00:18:46.172
I need to try to find a new place

00:18:46.631 --> 00:18:47.882
where I can continue my work.

00:18:48.383 --> 00:18:49.425
Thanks to you.

00:18:51.511 --> 00:18:52.512
Are you mad?

00:18:53.137 --> 00:18:54.137
Is that why...

00:18:54.597 --> 00:18:58.101
you're picking
on the photo of that innocent guy?

00:19:03.147 --> 00:19:04.147
Nope.

00:19:04.440 --> 00:19:06.484
The word "innocent" doesn't suit him.

00:19:07.569 --> 00:19:09.904
He’s anything but innocent!

00:19:11.030 --> 00:19:13.116
The word "despicable" suits him better.

00:19:13.783 --> 00:19:16.286
If you run into this person
in the hallway,

00:19:17.537 --> 00:19:18.830
you better hide.

00:19:25.587 --> 00:19:26.629
I'm tired.

00:19:27.297 --> 00:19:28.586
I'm going to sleep.

00:19:29.143 --> 00:19:30.143
Later.

00:19:45.846 --> 00:19:47.473
My club needs to have another member.

00:19:47.854 --> 00:19:50.024
Or else, they’ll take away my club room.

00:20:50.713 --> 00:20:52.422
A true journalist

00:20:52.423 --> 00:20:55.050
is someone who does not just report

00:20:55.051 --> 00:20:57.220
but exposes the truth.

00:20:57.845 --> 00:21:02.850
The truth about what
affects us, the public.

00:21:03.434 --> 00:21:06.521
Unfortunately, the exposition isn’t enough.

00:21:06.980 --> 00:21:09.147
Things need to be well-researched,

00:21:09.148 --> 00:21:10.524
investigated

00:21:10.525 --> 00:21:11.818
and in all angles.

00:21:12.443 --> 00:21:14.696
This is my dream for all of you.

00:21:16.030 --> 00:21:19.909
You are the next generation
of storytellers

00:21:20.451 --> 00:21:22.703
who are committed to the truth

00:21:22.704 --> 00:21:25.747
and it is backed up by facts.

00:21:25.748 --> 00:21:27.417
So for your activity,

00:21:27.667 --> 00:21:29.252
let us put into action

00:21:29.502 --> 00:21:32.422
everything we discussed about research.

00:21:33.047 --> 00:21:34.882
Think of a story

00:21:35.508 --> 00:21:38.052
that piques your interest.

00:21:38.553 --> 00:21:41.431
And of course,
when you submit and present it,

00:21:42.140 --> 00:21:45.601
make sure it's backed up by research.

00:21:45.852 --> 00:21:46.477
Ma’am!

00:21:46.644 --> 00:21:48.229
What type of topic?

00:21:48.396 --> 00:21:49.396
Anything!

00:21:50.148 --> 00:21:52.608
Something that sparks your curiosity.

00:21:52.900 --> 00:21:53.609
Understood?

00:21:53.860 --> 00:21:55.485
Yes, ma'am.

00:21:55.486 --> 00:21:57.155
All right. Now, go to your groups.

00:21:59.198 --> 00:22:02.159
What if we make
the emergence of AI our topic instead?

00:22:02.160 --> 00:22:04.953
If it’s okay to use in school or at work.

00:22:04.954 --> 00:22:06.998
Advantages and disadvantages.

00:22:07.123 --> 00:22:08.249
Yeah, right.

00:22:09.375 --> 00:22:12.837
But I heard the other group
is also doing AI.

00:22:13.296 --> 00:22:15.173
What about you, girl? What do you think?

00:22:15.715 --> 00:22:19.093
Seriously? What if we think of a new topic?

00:22:19.552 --> 00:22:20.802
How about you, Lori?

00:22:20.803 --> 00:22:24.265
Do you have any topic in mind
that the other groups haven’t thought of?

00:22:25.475 --> 00:22:26.475
Hmm...

00:22:28.102 --> 00:22:29.102
What if..

00:22:29.771 --> 00:22:31.105
Mental health?

00:22:31.856 --> 00:22:35.068
Right? It’s relevant, after all.

00:22:35.276 --> 00:22:37.152
Especially after all the incidents.

00:22:37.153 --> 00:22:38.738
For example, what happened with Lisa.

00:22:39.697 --> 00:22:41.657
Maybe we can focus on..

00:22:41.991 --> 00:22:43.200
What are the usual signs

00:22:43.201 --> 00:22:45.787
that a person struggling
with his or her mental health?

00:22:46.496 --> 00:22:49.957
Basically, the importance
of this research is to inform

00:22:50.208 --> 00:22:52.460
and to give awareness to everyone.

00:22:53.252 --> 00:22:56.506
So that if they have loved ones

00:22:56.881 --> 00:22:58.007
who are struggling,

00:22:58.716 --> 00:23:00.052
they’ll know how to handle it.

00:23:04.514 --> 00:23:07.557
I feel like we’ve got our topic. Perfect!

00:23:07.558 --> 00:23:09.060
I know right, girl!

00:23:09.435 --> 00:23:11.311
Yeah. Let’s go with that one.

00:23:11.312 --> 00:23:12.312
Nice one!

00:23:13.564 --> 00:23:15.107
Sounds good. Let's go?

00:23:15.108 --> 00:23:16.109
- Let’s start?
- Yeah.

00:23:18.486 --> 00:23:19.612
Alright.

00:23:25.576 --> 00:23:26.618
That’s Lori!

00:23:26.619 --> 00:23:28.703
- Yeah, you’re right!
- Come on! Let’s go to Lori!

00:23:28.704 --> 00:23:29.704
Excuse me!

00:23:32.083 --> 00:23:33.084
Lori!

00:23:33.417 --> 00:23:34.168
Hey!

00:23:34.293 --> 00:23:35.627
Why are you eating by yourself?

00:23:35.628 --> 00:23:37.672
- I thought we were having lunch together.
- Hi, Lori!

00:23:38.005 --> 00:23:38.881
Sorry!

00:23:38.882 --> 00:23:40.466
I got hungry.

00:23:40.716 --> 00:23:42.093
We’ll join you.

00:23:43.803 --> 00:23:45.972
So, have you chosen a club to join?

00:23:46.472 --> 00:23:48.057
I haven’t decided yet.

00:23:48.599 --> 00:23:50.768
Since you’re still having
a hard time deciding,

00:23:51.102 --> 00:23:53.186
come join me
in the Paranormal Club for now.

00:23:53.187 --> 00:23:54.396
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

00:23:54.397 --> 00:23:56.523
- Come on, join us.
- Yeah, Lori.

00:23:56.524 --> 00:23:57.524
It's fun.

00:23:57.650 --> 00:24:00.485
Since there are more of us now,

00:24:00.486 --> 00:24:02.779
and I’m sure I’m transferring there,

00:24:02.780 --> 00:24:03.989
it won’t be scary anymore.

00:24:03.990 --> 00:24:05.157
There are many of us.

00:24:05.158 --> 00:24:08.411
Plus, didn’t you say
you wanted something chill?

00:24:08.661 --> 00:24:10.495
See? It’s chilling.

00:24:10.496 --> 00:24:12.957
- Promise.
- Chilling.

00:24:13.124 --> 00:24:15.459
Are you guys really sure
about the Paranormal Club?

00:24:15.668 --> 00:24:17.711
Don’t you want the Q.E.D. Club?

00:24:17.712 --> 00:24:19.629
- Huh?
- That’s an adventure, too.

00:24:19.630 --> 00:24:22.133
- I don’t want there. It feels weird.
- Right.

00:24:22.675 --> 00:24:24.509
That club’s probably cursed or something.

00:24:24.510 --> 00:24:26.053
It only has one member.

00:24:26.512 --> 00:24:30.682
Ah, maybe no one joins
because it’s cursed.

00:24:30.683 --> 00:24:31.684
You think so?

00:24:36.355 --> 00:24:37.355
Wait.

00:24:37.523 --> 00:24:40.295
Are you sure
you’re really hunting a ghost?

00:24:40.443 --> 00:24:41.402
Yes!

00:24:41.403 --> 00:24:45.114
Maybe there’s really nothing to hunt.

00:24:45.838 --> 00:24:48.257
Sometimes there’s nothing.
But sometimes there is!

00:24:48.584 --> 00:24:51.411
They said before the main quest,

00:24:51.412 --> 00:24:54.457
the club has to do a dry run
at a haunted apartment.

00:24:54.874 --> 00:24:56.458
- Really?
- Yes.

00:24:56.459 --> 00:24:58.711
Someone actually suggested a hunting spot.

00:24:59.420 --> 00:25:00.838
He used to live there.

00:25:01.130 --> 00:25:02.465
It’s just three blocks away.

00:25:02.965 --> 00:25:03.965
But...

00:25:04.217 --> 00:25:06.510
he had no choice but to move out.

00:25:07.011 --> 00:25:08.262
Three blocks away.

00:25:08.930 --> 00:25:11.140
Isn’t that Tita Martha’s apartment?

00:25:11.933 --> 00:25:14.894
The story goes
that when he’s taking a bath,

00:25:15.144 --> 00:25:18.688
he says he hears someone calling his name.

00:25:18.689 --> 00:25:20.733
And asking for help.

00:25:21.150 --> 00:25:22.150
Right?

00:25:22.443 --> 00:25:23.486
There’s more.

00:25:24.237 --> 00:25:25.988
When he’s asleep...

00:25:26.322 --> 00:25:29.450
he hears banging and rustling sounds.

00:25:31.410 --> 00:25:33.677
Oh, scary!

00:25:34.949 --> 00:25:36.743
What's the name of that apartment?

00:25:37.124 --> 00:25:38.536
They said it’s Henson Apartment.

00:25:41.122 --> 00:25:42.165
Are you okay?

00:25:42.964 --> 00:25:43.964
I’m okay, but...

00:25:44.257 --> 00:25:45.216
Henson Apartment?

00:25:45.217 --> 00:25:47.575
I'm sorry to tell you,
but there’s no ghost there.

00:25:48.010 --> 00:25:50.554
Maybe it was just his imagination.

00:25:51.264 --> 00:25:52.890
What makes you say that?

00:25:53.015 --> 00:25:54.432
Because I live there.

00:25:54.433 --> 00:25:56.017
I’ve been there for almost a month.

00:25:56.018 --> 00:25:57.812
Nothing's happened to me.

00:25:58.104 --> 00:25:59.104
Oh, really?

00:25:59.105 --> 00:26:00.273
Yeah. Nothing at all.

00:26:00.690 --> 00:26:02.024
Even...

00:26:02.483 --> 00:26:03.734
my roommate.

00:26:03.891 --> 00:26:07.528
He said he hasn’t felt any ghost there.

00:26:07.792 --> 00:26:09.127
You can’t be sure either.

00:26:09.282 --> 00:26:10.574
Maybe there really is something.

00:26:11.200 --> 00:26:13.326
You just didn’t explore enough.

00:26:13.327 --> 00:26:15.329
Yeah, maybe you’re just in denial.

00:26:15.538 --> 00:26:16.830
Exactly!

00:26:16.831 --> 00:26:19.082
Maybe once we bring the equipment,

00:26:19.083 --> 00:26:20.418
that’s when things will show up.

00:26:21.669 --> 00:26:22.752
I really don’t want to.

00:26:22.753 --> 00:26:24.171
They do have a point.

00:26:24.797 --> 00:26:25.797
Come on.

00:26:25.965 --> 00:26:26.924
Join us.

00:26:26.924 --> 00:26:27.800
Join us already.

00:26:27.883 --> 00:26:28.925
Come on.

00:26:28.926 --> 00:26:29.885
Come on, Lori.

00:26:29.886 --> 00:26:30.969
Lori!

00:26:30.970 --> 00:26:31.929
Lori!

00:26:31.930 --> 00:26:34.347
Lori! Lori! Lori!

00:26:34.348 --> 00:26:37.435
Lori! Lori! Lori! Lori!

00:26:42.815 --> 00:26:44.317
Lorelei...

00:26:46.402 --> 00:26:47.903
Lorelei...

00:26:47.945 --> 00:26:49.155
Tita Martha?

00:26:56.120 --> 00:26:57.121
Lori...

00:26:57.913 --> 00:26:59.832
Help me, Lori.

00:27:00.958 --> 00:27:02.209
Lori!

00:27:03.044 --> 00:27:04.837
Help me, Lori!

00:27:04.879 --> 00:27:06.839
Tita Martha, why?

00:28:16.909 --> 00:28:19.995
Lori! Help me, Lori!

00:28:25.501 --> 00:28:26.501
Oh, my God.

00:29:09.044 --> 00:29:10.379
Don’t you ever rinse?

00:29:10.713 --> 00:29:12.590
I hear something.

00:29:13.424 --> 00:29:15.383
It sounds like an old woman’s voice.

00:29:15.384 --> 00:29:17.094
It’s calling out my name.

00:29:17.803 --> 00:29:19.180
It’s asking for help.

00:29:34.737 --> 00:29:35.821
There’s nothing in there.

00:29:36.197 --> 00:29:37.197
You’re just tired.

00:29:37.364 --> 00:29:40.159
Loki, I promise, I really hear something.

00:29:41.410 --> 00:29:43.871
Ghosts don’t exist. Okay?

00:29:44.914 --> 00:29:45.914
But...

00:29:48.083 --> 00:29:49.083
Okay.

00:29:49.835 --> 00:29:50.835
Nevermind.

00:29:51.170 --> 00:29:52.296
I believe you.

00:29:53.964 --> 00:29:54.964
Thanks.

00:30:02.264 --> 00:30:03.723
Why is it me?

00:30:03.724 --> 00:30:05.851
Why is it asking me for help?

00:30:06.227 --> 00:30:08.728
What kind of help can I give

00:30:08.729 --> 00:30:11.440
if I can't even help myself?

00:30:11.857 --> 00:30:13.692
Honestly, I'm scared.

00:30:14.109 --> 00:30:16.487
I don’t want to believe
that woman’s voice.

00:30:16.695 --> 00:30:18.821
But if I ever believe it...

00:30:18.822 --> 00:30:21.158
I hope it's your voice I hear.

00:30:21.534 --> 00:30:22.576
- My child...
- Why is it me?

00:30:23.077 --> 00:30:24.286
Smile.

00:30:24.745 --> 00:30:25.955
That’s it.

00:30:26.288 --> 00:30:28.666
Show me your teeth. Beautiful smile!

00:30:32.336 --> 00:30:34.755
Why is she asking me for help?

00:30:36.340 --> 00:30:40.511
How can I help someone,
if I can’t even help myself?

00:30:48.727 --> 00:30:51.564
I don’t know what to do without you, Mom.

00:30:55.150 --> 00:30:56.402
I miss you.

00:31:18.757 --> 00:31:21.844
Lorelei, help me. I'm begging you.

00:31:23.512 --> 00:31:24.512
What is it now?

00:31:25.848 --> 00:31:28.142
I heard an old woman’s voice

00:31:28.225 --> 00:31:29.435
in my room.

00:31:30.978 --> 00:31:31.979
Why?

00:31:32.229 --> 00:31:33.855
What are you laughing at?

00:31:33.856 --> 00:31:35.524
I’m serious, Loki.

00:31:35.858 --> 00:31:37.026
It's true!

00:31:40.708 --> 00:31:41.751
It's almost 10:00.

00:31:42.698 --> 00:31:43.782
Just sleep it off.

00:31:44.116 --> 00:31:45.159
It'll go away.

00:31:45.534 --> 00:31:46.577
Are you sure?

00:31:47.202 --> 00:31:48.661
You really don’t see

00:31:48.662 --> 00:31:51.999
or hear or feel anything strange?

00:31:54.126 --> 00:31:55.169
Mind over matter.

00:31:55.836 --> 00:31:59.006
If you really believe there’s a ghost,
then you’ll see one.

00:32:00.174 --> 00:32:01.634
So annoying.

00:32:02.635 --> 00:32:03.719
My God.

00:32:10.225 --> 00:32:12.019
Help me, Lori.

00:32:16.106 --> 00:32:18.275
Please leave me alone.

00:32:18.525 --> 00:32:19.902
Whoever you are.

00:32:20.217 --> 00:32:21.217
Lori.

00:32:21.945 --> 00:32:23.739
Help me, Lori.

00:32:24.448 --> 00:32:26.116
I'm begging you, too.

00:32:27.409 --> 00:32:29.036
Let me sleep.

00:32:30.120 --> 00:32:33.540
If you want,
go bother my friend Rosetta instead.

00:32:34.541 --> 00:32:35.584
Lori...

00:32:37.419 --> 00:32:38.170
Lori...

00:32:38.171 --> 00:32:40.005
Help me, Lori.

00:32:41.840 --> 00:32:43.258
Lori...

00:32:43.425 --> 00:32:45.552
Lori. Help me, Lori.

00:32:46.637 --> 00:32:47.721
Lori...

00:32:48.222 --> 00:32:50.349
Lori. Help me, Lori.

00:32:54.978 --> 00:32:57.398
Lori. Help me, Lori.

00:32:58.774 --> 00:33:00.984
Lori. Help me, Lori.

00:33:01.193 --> 00:33:02.193
I...

00:33:03.028 --> 00:33:04.780
I'm begging you.

00:33:05.739 --> 00:33:07.658
I'm begging you.

00:33:08.951 --> 00:33:10.994
I'm begging you.

00:33:11.412 --> 00:33:13.414
Lori. Help me, Lori.

00:33:13.622 --> 00:33:15.624
I'm begging you.

00:33:16.750 --> 00:33:18.377
Help me, Lori.

00:33:20.295 --> 00:33:21.964
Help me, Lori.

00:33:22.923 --> 00:33:25.508
Help me, Lori.

00:33:25.509 --> 00:33:26.677
Lori...

00:33:27.845 --> 00:33:29.847
Lori. Help me, Lori.

00:33:30.723 --> 00:33:31.682
Lori.

00:33:31.683 --> 00:33:33.434
Help me, Lori.

00:33:34.518 --> 00:33:35.936
Lori.

00:33:36.926 --> 00:33:38.261
Help me, Lori.

00:33:38.286 --> 00:33:39.496
Lori.

00:33:39.741 --> 00:33:42.494
Lori. Help me, Lori.

00:33:43.819 --> 00:33:45.195
Lori.

00:33:46.113 --> 00:33:47.948
Lori. Help me, Lori.

00:33:47.990 --> 00:33:50.968
- Whose hair is this?
- Lori.

00:33:50.993 --> 00:33:52.953
Lori. Help me, Lori.

00:33:53.162 --> 00:33:54.246
Over and over again.

00:33:57.124 --> 00:33:58.667
Same intonation.

00:34:01.044 --> 00:34:03.130
Same stress in the syllables.

00:34:04.256 --> 00:34:06.383
Lori. Help me, Lori.

00:34:08.135 --> 00:34:09.303
Recorded.

00:34:10.763 --> 00:34:12.222
The voice is recorded.

00:34:13.599 --> 00:34:14.767
Lori.

00:34:15.866 --> 00:34:18.661
Lori. Help me, Lori.

00:34:20.439 --> 00:34:23.233
Lori. Help me, Lori.

00:34:25.235 --> 00:34:26.779
Lori.

00:34:27.487 --> 00:34:29.155
Lori. Help me.

00:34:31.567 --> 00:34:34.362
Lori. Help me, Lori.

00:34:37.080 --> 00:34:39.875
Lori. Help me, Lori.

00:34:42.106 --> 00:34:44.900
Lori. Help me, Lori.

00:34:52.888 --> 00:34:53.930
Have you gone mad?

00:34:53.931 --> 00:34:54.907
Mad?

00:34:54.932 --> 00:34:57.559
Yes, I’m really mad at what you did!

00:34:59.673 --> 00:35:00.549
What did I do to you?

00:35:00.574 --> 00:35:02.617
Don’t mess with me, Loki.

00:35:03.857 --> 00:35:05.275
What you said was right.

00:35:05.567 --> 00:35:07.820
Ghosts don't exist in this unit.

00:35:08.612 --> 00:35:09.612
See?

00:35:09.863 --> 00:35:10.781
Told you.

00:35:10.782 --> 00:35:14.367
But what the old woman’s voice I hear
when I’m showering

00:35:14.368 --> 00:35:15.953
and while I'm in the room...

00:35:16.286 --> 00:35:17.871
that was you, wasn't it?

00:35:19.706 --> 00:35:21.266
I don’t know what you’re talking about.

00:35:21.333 --> 00:35:23.376
Please enlighten me.

00:35:23.377 --> 00:35:24.378
Really?

00:35:24.962 --> 00:35:26.755
Then how would you explain this?

00:35:27.256 --> 00:35:28.215
What is that?

00:35:28.216 --> 00:35:31.677
So I found a strand of hair on my floor,
just a minute ago.

00:35:32.094 --> 00:35:34.346
It’s only about two to three inches long.

00:35:34.596 --> 00:35:36.722
There’s no way that came from my hair.

00:35:36.723 --> 00:35:39.434
It’s too long, and the color’s different!

00:35:39.893 --> 00:35:41.727
It’s not Tita Martha’s either,

00:35:41.728 --> 00:35:43.480
since her hair’s kind of long.

00:35:43.897 --> 00:35:47.442
Of the three of us
who have access to this unit,

00:35:47.901 --> 00:35:50.028
only you could own this.

00:35:51.029 --> 00:35:52.029
Are you sure?

00:35:52.155 --> 00:35:54.824
What does that have to do
with the voice you heard in your room?

00:35:54.825 --> 00:35:57.201
This is proof you were in my room

00:35:57.202 --> 00:36:00.184
and you planted the tape recorder
under my bed!

00:36:03.125 --> 00:36:04.876
You recorded your voice and distorted it,

00:36:04.877 --> 00:36:07.753
so would sound old
and I wouldn’t recognize it.

00:36:07.754 --> 00:36:08.754
Lori.

00:36:09.325 --> 00:36:10.576
Help me, Lori.

00:36:11.174 --> 00:36:12.718
Lori. Help me, Lori.

00:36:14.344 --> 00:36:15.344
Lori.

00:36:15.554 --> 00:36:16.762
Lori.

00:36:16.763 --> 00:36:19.308
Lori. Help me, Lori.

00:36:19.850 --> 00:36:20.850
Lori.

00:36:21.499 --> 00:36:24.294
You wanted to scare me,
so you did that, right?

00:36:31.570 --> 00:36:33.780
When you hid that tape recorder
under my bed

00:36:34.281 --> 00:36:36.782
you didn’t expect for me
to find a strand of your hair.

00:36:36.783 --> 00:36:37.783
Did you?

00:36:43.832 --> 00:36:45.751
Now that I think about it...

00:36:46.960 --> 00:36:50.380
your previous roommates
experienced the exact same thing.

00:36:51.423 --> 00:36:52.423
So…

00:36:52.674 --> 00:36:55.614
is it possible that you played
the same prank on them

00:36:55.928 --> 00:36:57.512
to make them move out

00:36:57.638 --> 00:37:00.057
so you could have this whole unit
to yourself?

00:37:00.682 --> 00:37:01.682
What?

00:37:02.017 --> 00:37:03.185
Am I right?

00:37:14.071 --> 00:37:15.071
Bravo!

00:37:16.782 --> 00:37:19.075
I did not expect you to figure it out

00:37:19.076 --> 00:37:20.452
in a matter of hours.

00:37:21.995 --> 00:37:23.330
And just to be clear,

00:37:24.039 --> 00:37:25.499
it was my intention

00:37:25.874 --> 00:37:27.751
to leave a strand of hair in your room.

00:37:29.461 --> 00:37:31.922
I want to know
if you’ll be able to notice it

00:37:32.339 --> 00:37:34.633
so you can connect it
to the tape recording.

00:37:38.762 --> 00:37:39.846
And...

00:37:40.430 --> 00:37:42.182
you failed to disappoint me.

00:37:44.518 --> 00:37:45.978
Think of it as a test.

00:37:46.812 --> 00:37:48.355
- Test?
- Yeah.

00:37:48.730 --> 00:37:50.190
To scare me?

00:37:50.691 --> 00:37:53.193
So you can force me out of this unit?

00:37:54.903 --> 00:37:56.238
Part of it, yes.

00:37:57.906 --> 00:37:59.323
I want to know

00:37:59.324 --> 00:38:02.244
if you deserve to stay in this unit.

00:38:03.161 --> 00:38:04.161
And...

00:38:04.997 --> 00:38:06.289
I want to know...

00:38:07.416 --> 00:38:09.167
if my hunch about you is correct.

00:38:09.501 --> 00:38:10.711
What hunch?

00:38:11.378 --> 00:38:12.462
That you

00:38:13.088 --> 00:38:16.842
have above average observation skills.

00:38:19.094 --> 00:38:20.762
While I was reading your blog,

00:38:21.179 --> 00:38:25.480
I noticed how detailed you were
in describing every moment.

00:38:26.268 --> 00:38:28.186
You never let anything slide.

00:38:28.770 --> 00:38:30.439
I find that very impressive.

00:38:30.897 --> 00:38:31.982
So why?

00:38:32.274 --> 00:38:34.234
What do you need to confirm?

00:38:35.777 --> 00:38:37.362
That you deserve...

00:38:38.280 --> 00:38:39.531
to join my club.

00:38:40.824 --> 00:38:42.451
The result of my test on you

00:38:42.951 --> 00:38:44.578
made me want to recruit you more.

00:38:45.377 --> 00:38:46.837
Recruit my foot!

00:38:50.300 --> 00:38:51.333
Oh!

00:38:53.045 --> 00:38:54.755
So you’re rejecting my offer?

00:38:55.589 --> 00:38:57.506
Is that why you’ve been avoiding me
since yesterday

00:38:57.507 --> 00:38:59.543
at school and even here in the apartment?

00:39:00.177 --> 00:39:02.888
Excuse me, I'm not avoiding you!

00:39:04.514 --> 00:39:05.515
Are you sure?

00:39:07.059 --> 00:39:09.144
Based on the actions you’ve shown...

00:39:10.228 --> 00:39:13.398
you are showing an Avoidance Behavior.

00:39:13.899 --> 00:39:15.817
What are you even saying?

00:39:16.193 --> 00:39:17.778
It’s a form of defense mechanism

00:39:18.195 --> 00:39:20.780
where a person avoids certain situations

00:39:20.781 --> 00:39:24.534
that cause stress, fear,
and uneasy emotions.

00:39:27.204 --> 00:39:30.457
Oh, my God, can you please stop
psycho-analyzing my actions?

00:39:30.999 --> 00:39:34.502
Also, can you ask me
for a different favor instead?

00:39:34.503 --> 00:39:36.213
Let’s not talk about me joining the club.

00:39:37.130 --> 00:39:39.216
If you keep insisting on what you want

00:39:39.812 --> 00:39:42.273
sorry, but I can’t give it to you.

00:39:45.013 --> 00:39:46.055
Did you hear me?

00:39:46.056 --> 00:39:47.307
I said no!

00:39:48.266 --> 00:39:49.518
Yeah, I heard you.

00:39:51.228 --> 00:39:53.105
But you’re leaving me
with no other choice.

00:39:53.522 --> 00:39:54.731
What do you mean?

00:39:58.527 --> 00:39:59.486
How dare you!

00:39:59.487 --> 00:40:00.611
Delete that!

00:40:00.612 --> 00:40:01.947
How did you get that?

00:40:02.072 --> 00:40:04.699
You went into my room
without my permission?

00:40:05.033 --> 00:40:07.077
You should have installed more locks
on your door.

00:40:11.665 --> 00:40:12.833
Look at your photo.

00:40:13.333 --> 00:40:16.169
You probably won’t like it
if this spreads on social media.

00:40:16.586 --> 00:40:18.338
Are you blackmailing me?

00:40:18.463 --> 00:40:19.463
Am I?

00:40:20.257 --> 00:40:22.217
It doesn’t matter to me
as long it does the trick.

00:40:22.759 --> 00:40:24.969
Loki, I'm telling you!

00:40:24.970 --> 00:40:26.221
I dare you!

00:40:26.596 --> 00:40:28.180
I dare you.

00:40:28.181 --> 00:40:29.181
Loki!

00:40:30.350 --> 00:40:32.101
That’s a threat, you know.

00:40:32.102 --> 00:40:34.062
But you know what, go ahead.

00:40:34.271 --> 00:40:35.480
Post it.

00:40:35.939 --> 00:40:37.274
I don’t care.

00:40:37.941 --> 00:40:39.192
I’m not threatening you.

00:40:40.110 --> 00:40:41.670
I’m just reminding you of your promise.

00:40:43.071 --> 00:40:44.864
You said that you’re willing to help Lara.

00:40:44.865 --> 00:40:45.866
Lisa!

00:40:46.116 --> 00:40:47.158
Whatever.

00:40:47.159 --> 00:40:48.743
But whoever that student is...

00:40:49.035 --> 00:40:50.829
you told me to help her.

00:40:50.996 --> 00:40:52.414
Because you feel guilty

00:40:52.664 --> 00:40:53.999
when you don’t help her.

00:40:54.749 --> 00:40:56.459
You felt somewhat responsible.

00:40:57.294 --> 00:40:59.838
Now, all I’m asking for is what you said.

00:41:01.576 --> 00:41:02.619
Are you really like that?

00:41:03.466 --> 00:41:04.743
You can’t keep your word?

00:41:19.900 --> 00:41:21.193
Are you really like that?

00:41:21.902 --> 00:41:23.695
You can’t keep your word, Lorelei?

00:41:29.701 --> 00:41:32.704
Loki’s like my ghost,
he never leaves me alone.

00:41:33.413 --> 00:41:35.040
I may not like his attitude,

00:41:35.749 --> 00:41:37.751
but everything he says is true.

00:41:38.877 --> 00:41:40.128
Which really scares me.

00:41:40.879 --> 00:41:41.879
A lot.

00:41:43.089 --> 00:41:46.218
I admit it, I’m afraid of being judged.

00:41:46.885 --> 00:41:48.845
I’m scared my life will get messed up.

00:41:49.471 --> 00:41:51.723
I’m scared the truth will hit me hard.

00:41:53.052 --> 00:41:54.804
But despite all these fears,

00:41:55.227 --> 00:41:56.895
there is one thing true.

00:41:57.479 --> 00:41:58.855
I want to help others.

00:41:59.439 --> 00:42:01.650
I may not able to face my own fears,

00:42:02.234 --> 00:42:04.861
but perhaps I can help others face theirs.

00:42:13.703 --> 00:42:18.249
Focus on your studies
and stay out of trouble at school.

00:42:18.250 --> 00:42:20.450
Focus on your studies
and stay out of trouble at school.

00:42:26.800 --> 00:42:27.800
Okay.

00:42:30.637 --> 00:42:31.972
Just do it, Lori.

00:42:32.847 --> 00:42:33.847
Okay.

00:42:39.020 --> 00:42:40.020
Loki?

00:42:43.942 --> 00:42:45.235
Loki, are you there?

00:43:39.831 --> 00:43:41.081
To: Rhea
Subject: Just checking on you.

00:43:41.082 --> 00:43:42.250
Message: How are you doing?

00:43:42.275 --> 00:43:44.903
It's been three weeks
since I sent my last email to you.

00:43:45.128 --> 00:43:47.088
And you still haven't gotten back to me.

00:43:47.297 --> 00:43:49.340
Either you've been too busy to check

00:43:49.341 --> 00:43:52.218
or you don't open your e-mail
as regularly as I do.

00:43:53.386 --> 00:43:54.471
In any case,

00:43:54.763 --> 00:43:57.515
I'm writing to express
how the status quo bores me.

00:43:57.974 --> 00:43:59.141
Without you,

00:43:59.142 --> 00:44:02.270
this world lacks the colors it once had
when you were around.

00:44:02.854 --> 00:44:04.981
It has become dull and monotonous.

00:44:05.565 --> 00:44:07.984
I wonder how long
I can endure the mundane.

00:44:11.488 --> 00:44:13.073
Of all the people who know me,

00:44:13.698 --> 00:44:14.865
you are the most aware

00:44:14.866 --> 00:44:18.286
of how much I abhor
the dismal routine of existence.

00:44:19.454 --> 00:44:21.414
Everything is so ordinary.

00:44:22.123 --> 00:44:23.666
Everyone is so boring.

00:44:24.501 --> 00:44:26.002
And everything is so grey.

00:44:26.711 --> 00:44:29.589
I’ve been searching
for an added tinge of color in my life.

00:44:30.340 --> 00:44:33.593
But it has always escaped my grasp
ever since you left.

00:44:34.511 --> 00:44:35.594
You would surely agree with me

00:44:35.595 --> 00:44:38.098
when I say
that I need to find a distraction.

00:44:39.140 --> 00:44:42.310
An escape from this repetitive
and depressing reality.

00:44:43.103 --> 00:44:44.646
If you were only here,

00:44:45.438 --> 00:44:47.524
it would still be a lot of fun
and challenging.

00:44:49.484 --> 00:44:53.154
I always found your opposition
to my views thought-provoking.

00:44:54.322 --> 00:44:55.322
Now...

00:44:55.824 --> 00:44:57.783
I’m in a constant pursuit of diversion

00:44:57.784 --> 00:45:00.870
to keep my mind stimulated
and my monsters at bay.

00:45:02.163 --> 00:45:03.873
It may be an endless chase...

00:45:04.666 --> 00:45:07.001
and I don’t know
if it’s a worthwhile quest, but...

00:45:07.919 --> 00:45:10.505
this is the best alternative
I have so far.

00:45:11.714 --> 00:45:13.716
I look forward to hearing your stories.

00:45:15.427 --> 00:45:17.429
Please get back to me as soon as you can.

00:45:19.389 --> 00:45:20.389
Regards,

00:45:21.599 --> 00:45:22.434
Loki.

00:45:22.775 --> 00:45:24.527
Your curiosity would have you killed!

00:45:25.228 --> 00:45:26.229
Do you know that?

00:45:27.397 --> 00:45:29.732
Why did you just suddenly show up?

00:45:33.111 --> 00:45:37.740
I don’t remember giving you permission
to read my personal messages.

00:45:40.034 --> 00:45:42.162
That's a clear invasion of privacy!

00:45:44.456 --> 00:45:45.540
Yeah, right!

00:45:46.040 --> 00:45:48.292
Coming from someone
who was peeking at my messages

00:45:48.293 --> 00:45:49.627
while I was reading them.

00:45:49.752 --> 00:45:51.632
And someone
who comes into my room late at night

00:45:51.796 --> 00:45:54.548
to take pictures of me
while I was sleeping

00:45:54.549 --> 00:45:56.134
without my consent.

00:46:03.600 --> 00:46:05.768
You’re probably here
to join the Q.E.D. Club.

00:46:09.105 --> 00:46:10.105
Here’s the form.

00:46:10.982 --> 00:46:11.982
Fill it out.

00:46:48.895 --> 00:46:49.895
Are we good?

00:46:51.731 --> 00:46:53.233
Okay, quick orientation.

00:46:53.608 --> 00:46:56.110
The Q.E.D. Club

00:46:56.611 --> 00:47:00.114
is the one and only detective club
in Clark University.

00:47:00.490 --> 00:47:02.170
Its name is derived from the Latin phrase,

00:47:02.659 --> 00:47:06.621
Quod Erat Demonstrandum.

00:47:07.288 --> 00:47:08.706
Which means in English,

00:47:08.915 --> 00:47:10.959
“Which was to be demonstrated."

00:47:11.626 --> 00:47:14.546
That’s usually placed
at the end of math proofs

00:47:14.879 --> 00:47:16.672
or philosophical arguments

00:47:16.673 --> 00:47:20.009
to show that you’ve proven
what you set out to prove.

00:47:22.136 --> 00:47:23.513
Okay.

00:47:23.972 --> 00:47:25.482
Thanks for the info.

00:47:26.182 --> 00:47:28.476
So, what should I do?

00:47:29.269 --> 00:47:30.269
Well...

00:47:31.271 --> 00:47:34.148
our mission
is to investigate hidden truths...

00:47:35.567 --> 00:47:38.152
solve mysteries through logic and teamwork

00:47:38.444 --> 00:47:41.573
and protect the innocent
from deception and injustice.

00:47:42.240 --> 00:47:43.240
Noted.

00:47:43.908 --> 00:47:45.910
For your role, it’s pretty simple.

00:47:46.911 --> 00:47:49.789
You will help me collate requests
from clients.

00:47:49.914 --> 00:47:52.457
Once we’re in the investigation proper,

00:47:52.458 --> 00:47:54.877
I expect you to provide insights.

00:47:59.299 --> 00:48:02.135
I need you to observe more
in the case details,

00:48:02.343 --> 00:48:03.677
crime scenes,

00:48:03.678 --> 00:48:06.973
the people involved,
their stories and et cetera.

00:48:07.765 --> 00:48:08.765
And of course...

00:48:08.808 --> 00:48:11.227
don’t forget to take down notes
so we won’t miss anything.

00:48:12.353 --> 00:48:13.288
So...

00:48:13.313 --> 00:48:14.731
once we solve the case…

00:48:15.023 --> 00:48:17.483
your main task is to write about it

00:48:17.859 --> 00:48:19.444
and post it on your blog.

00:48:19.902 --> 00:48:20.902
Wait.

00:48:21.529 --> 00:48:22.988
So are you saying…

00:48:22.989 --> 00:48:25.617
you want me to be the club chronicler?

00:48:26.659 --> 00:48:27.744
Something like that.

00:48:28.870 --> 00:48:30.079
As you may notice

00:48:31.581 --> 00:48:33.583
the Q.E.D. Club isn’t popular yet

00:48:34.042 --> 00:48:35.460
among the students,

00:48:35.710 --> 00:48:38.087
freshmen and transferees.

00:48:39.297 --> 00:48:41.257
We can use your writing skills

00:48:41.591 --> 00:48:43.718
to advertise our club.

00:48:44.510 --> 00:48:45.803
Boost our popularity

00:48:46.262 --> 00:48:48.306
and attract more clients.

00:48:50.683 --> 00:48:52.352
So as Vice President,

00:48:52.894 --> 00:48:56.481
you are in charge
of media and public relations.

00:48:57.649 --> 00:48:58.649
Wait.

00:48:58.983 --> 00:49:01.152
I’m the club Vice President?

00:49:01.736 --> 00:49:03.821
I didn’t sign up for this.

00:49:05.239 --> 00:49:07.116
I’m the President of this club.

00:49:07.785 --> 00:49:09.370
So as a second member,

00:49:09.744 --> 00:49:10.828
by default,

00:49:11.287 --> 00:49:13.056
you’re the Vice President now.

00:49:15.009 --> 00:49:17.418
For now, we will wait for a client

00:49:17.460 --> 00:49:19.170
to come and tell us their story.

00:49:20.171 --> 00:49:22.757
Or if you don’t have
the patience to wait...

00:49:24.217 --> 00:49:25.343
you can leave.

00:49:26.177 --> 00:49:27.891
I’ll message you when we have a case.

00:49:28.596 --> 00:49:31.140
Your contact number
is in the form anyway.

00:49:34.894 --> 00:49:36.396
So, that's it?

00:49:37.667 --> 00:49:39.794
You actually joined the Q.E.D. Club?

00:49:41.593 --> 00:49:43.095
I’m really sorry, Rosetta.

00:49:43.403 --> 00:49:46.030
I’m just not really
into paranormal things.

00:49:46.572 --> 00:49:47.699
Too bad.

00:49:48.700 --> 00:49:51.284
But if you change your mind,
let me know, okay?

00:49:51.285 --> 00:49:52.870
It’s fun there. I promise.

00:49:53.204 --> 00:49:54.204
Alright.

00:49:54.414 --> 00:49:55.414
Thank you, though.

00:49:56.040 --> 00:49:57.040
No problem.

00:49:57.458 --> 00:49:58.500
But, wait.

00:49:58.501 --> 00:50:02.171
Are you still going to continue
your ghost hunting at Henson Apartment?

00:50:02.505 --> 00:50:04.589
I’m telling you,
there are no ghosts there.

00:50:04.590 --> 00:50:06.230
You’ll probably just end up disappointed.

00:50:06.676 --> 00:50:09.262
Exactly. We’ll just look
for somewhere else.

00:50:11.806 --> 00:50:13.808
Oh, no! Our class is about to start!

00:50:14.392 --> 00:50:15.392
Huh?

00:50:15.643 --> 00:50:16.619
Let’s go!

00:50:16.644 --> 00:50:18.562
Why didn’t the lunch bell ring?

00:50:18.563 --> 00:50:20.148
Did you hear it?

00:50:20.440 --> 00:50:21.416
I didn’t either.

00:50:21.441 --> 00:50:22.441
Maybe it's broken?

00:50:25.903 --> 00:50:26.903
Come on.

00:50:26.946 --> 00:50:27.946
Let’s go.

00:50:30.074 --> 00:50:33.077
Hurry! Hurry! Let's go.

00:50:33.327 --> 00:50:36.329
Come on, we’re late for the next class.
Ma’am is already there.

00:50:36.354 --> 00:50:39.357
Oh, no. What's that? What's happening?

00:50:39.382 --> 00:50:41.300
- It's so crowded.
- What happened?

00:50:42.587 --> 00:50:43.963
Why is everyone freaking out?

00:50:45.339 --> 00:50:46.215
Excuse me.

00:50:46.215 --> 00:50:47.008
Excuse me.

00:50:47.008 --> 00:50:48.008
Excuse me.

00:50:51.053 --> 00:50:52.430
Come on, let's check it out.

00:50:52.680 --> 00:50:53.806
We’re going to be late.

00:50:54.056 --> 00:50:55.141
Just for a second.

00:51:10.448 --> 00:51:11.824
Get them out of here!

00:51:13.910 --> 00:51:15.578
Go back to your classrooms!

00:51:16.204 --> 00:51:18.498
Go back! Go back! Go back.

00:51:19.540 --> 00:51:21.167
- Go back to your classroom.
- Go ahead.

00:51:23.795 --> 00:51:25.337
Go back to your classroom.

00:51:25.338 --> 00:51:27.423
- Go. Come on.
- Go back, go back.

00:51:27.965 --> 00:51:28.965
Go back.

00:51:33.721 --> 00:51:36.390
Consider this
our first official case together.

00:51:36.415 --> 00:51:39.085
I'm Chief Gareth Estrada.

00:51:39.528 --> 00:51:40.737
Don’t just stand there.

00:51:40.895 --> 00:51:41.896
We got some work to do.

00:51:44.899 --> 00:51:46.108
Have you seen this, Chief?

00:51:46.484 --> 00:51:47.777
According here...

00:51:48.402 --> 00:51:53.485
Isaac texted three people
with the same message.

00:51:53.510 --> 00:51:57.704
I called you here
because your president was found dead.

00:52:02.158 --> 00:52:03.409
Does that mean...

00:52:03.709 --> 00:52:05.753
he was killed to silence him?

00:52:07.588 --> 00:52:10.299
Look, the post already
has a lot of reactions and comments!

00:52:14.220 --> 00:52:15.391
What happened to him?

00:52:15.721 --> 00:52:16.888
Why is he like that?

00:52:16.889 --> 00:52:18.057
Lorelei Rios?

00:52:19.684 --> 00:52:20.935
Be honest with me.

00:52:21.644 --> 00:52:23.396
Were you forced to join that club?